review_blob: Gold pour with white head, nice spicy aroma with good bitterness. Decent Pilsner brew.
Pitch black pour with light tan head. Licorice and possibly some chocolate tones. I did not like the finish on this one.
Light Blonde pour with thin white head. Very light on the hops for an IPA. Not very memorable.
Nice amber pour with thin white head, great malt flavor with perfect hop balance. Easy to drink.
Brilliant bloody red pour with nice white head. Very nice hop scent and flavor. Smooth finish, just like a bite from a vampire.
Not very hoppy for a Pale Ale. Was expecting a little more from Smuttynose since I enjoy a lot of their others
Very cloudy pumpkin color pour with thick white head, great hop aroma, clean finish. Very good IPA.
nice gold color with thin white head, great hop aroma and flavor. Very citrusy with some floral accents.
Ah I remember that blackout so well. Great pitch black pour with nice tan head, superb aromas of chocolate and coffee made this one of my favorite Russian Imperial Stouts
Dark amber pour with off white head, great malty flavor and nice arrangement of hops. Very easy to drink. Tasted great with pizza.

beer_brewer_name: Magic Hat Brewing Company (North American Breweries)
review_blob: Not impressed at all. Very watered down with not much flavor. Black pour with brown head, little aroma and very weak body.
beer_name: Magic Hat Matty OCohens Dry  Stout

review_blob: Never heard of this brewery but I must say this was a fantastic IPA. great caramel malt flavor with nice aromatic hops.
Amber pour with thin off white head, nice malt flavor but seemed a little lacking in hops for aroma and taste.
beer_name: Custom Brewcrafters St. Patricks Irish Ale

review_blob: Pitch black pour with tan head, great overall flavor, chocolate and coffee notes. One of my favorite stouts
Dark brown pour with light brown head, very cloudy almost murky appearance! Good overall flavor, very drinkable
Not bad, was expecting more spices as well with this winter ale. Amber pour with white head.
Fantastic seasonal from this brewery. Picked up a growler from my local store. Job well done Flying Bison
my favorite brew from my local home brewery, very drinkable brew, great aroma and flavor
beer_name: Flying Bison Skye Pilot Scotch Ale

review_blob: Local hometown brewery, nice pale ale, easy to drink, well balanced and nice aroma.
Dark pour leaving little head. Very strong alcohol taste but to be expected with this monster stout. Great beer for a dessert.. sip slowly
Amber pour with thin white head. Hops are as expected, strong alcohol taste but very well blended in this IIPA. Another great beer from Dogfish
Fantastic!! Everything I was expecting with this beer. Dark pour with near white head, coffee and chicory is a great pairing. Smooth taste and finish.

Great chocolate, expresso stout. I didnt taste much difference of the white chocolate but it was very tasty. Black pour and no head, the expresso flavor was a good mix with the chocolate. One of my favorite Expresso Stouts
beer_name: Rocky River White Chocolate Espresso Stout

review_blob: Local brewery for me which is nice to see. This lager was long waited for by me and I appreciate the overall flavor, characteristics of this brew.
3rd beer from this brewery, taste was a medium bodied, light caramel; clean tasting; citrus hop finish, not bad, my favorite of the 3.
beer_name: Erie Brewing Mad Anthonys Pale Ale

review_blob: Pale gold pour with very thin head. 2nd beer I have had from this brewery and I have not been to fond of the overall flavor.
Not much flavor but had a very smooth finish, weak hops, not at all what I was expecting
Gold color pour with no head. Interesting taste to say the least. Almost like a Non Alcoholic beer. Not terrible but if I needed to drink gluten free beer, this would be ok.
Deep brown nearly black in color. Malt aroma, coffee/chocolate flavor that is very smooth. Nice hop flavor. Overall a very good beer.
Great hop flavor, nice dark amber pour with long lasting head. Great seasonal brew for the holidays. Will definitely drink more of this one.
It looks like Guinness very close though not as smooth as Guinness but it seems more bitter and not as thick.
Creamy head and palate, same feel as guinness with a  milder ale, but overall not a bad tasting beer.
Poured amber with an average creamy white had that was lasting. Good hoppy aroma. Medium body with good hop flavor with a medium bitter finish. Very drinkable beer.
beer_name: Southern Tier PMX (Phin & Matts Extraordinary Ale)

review_blob: amber pour with white head, chocolate, brown sugar undertones. Not a bad seasonal, very drinkable
Pours a light copper with a white head. Malt is most noticeable in the aroma, not much hops. Flavor is ok but very lacking for a Pale Ale in my opinion
beer_name: Green Valley Brewing Stone Mill Pale Ale

review_blob: dark amber pour, molasses and raisen notes, great chocolate/coffee finish, love the added ginger as well. started to see more beers add ginger to their brews
outstanding IPA, great hop mixtures. Have to appreciate the aromas from one of the best IPAs on the market.
definitely not what I was expecting compared to their Nut Brown Ale. I was hoping this lager to follow suit, but it failed miserably.
beer_name: Samuel Smiths Pure Brewed Organic Lager

review_blob: great tasting brown ale, dark brown pour with thin laced head, nice walnut aroma, smooth aftertaste
not much of a head on this one after the pour. Dark amber color, very smooth to drink but not a ton characteristics I was expecting.
love ths spice combination for this seasonal brew, dark amber pour with very thin white head. Great for winter.

The Lagunita sales rep brought a keg of this to my local pub and had a beer tasting event.
Good IPA, nice smooth flavor and decent finish.
Not a bad lager, very smooth malt flavor with mild hops. Overall its a very drinkable lager but there are better ones out there.
Pour is a deep amber, the aroma is sweet and malty. Flavor is smooth with some spicy hops and a nice hoppy finish
2006 Ceramic bottle, great aroma of chocolate and coffee, dark black pour with tan head, lingering finish of licorice
nice malt flavor, smooth finish, wished for a bit more hops but overall a decent brew
smooth octoberfest, nice aroma, amber coloring, clean finish, wish it had a little more hops to it, but very drinkable
fantastic IPA from Stone, they never seem to disappoint me with any of their brews. Great hop aroma, taste, finish
light amber pour with medium off white head, nice citrus flavor with decent hoppiness, smooth finish.

beer_brewer_name: Magic Hat Brewing Company (North American Breweries)
review_blob: great fall beer, love the smoke flavor in this one, always pars well with a good BBQ
